Req. ID: 279101 
The VP, Global Customer Engineering role is a key management role reporting directly into the SVP of Worldwide Sales. The successful candidate will own objectives related to our ability to deliver compelling, highly technical customer engagements in the field. The successful candidate will work to deliver a world class customer experience, as they remove barriers to adoption and increase customer productivity. They will offer strategic leadership to help Micron transform the customer experience, working collaboratively across the company, to create innovative and meaningful customer outcomes. 
The successful candidate will be responsible for leading and developing the world-wide team of Field Applications Engineers, Solution Architects and Customer Labs that provides technical expertise and value to customers who integrate Micron products with their own. This person will serve as an internal thought leader and will participate in setting customer engagement strategy as well as having a significant operational and strategic impact. 
Qualifications: 
Ability to set the direction for a system and application driven engagement 
Experience working with customers in evaluating customer requirements, early engagement to enable product definitions and execution of Design Wins. Existing relationships with customers and demonstrated ability to influence key decision makers is expected 
Experience in engaging with CxO staff, presenting the voice of the customer and the market, driving and influencing decisions among internal leadership 
Demonstrated people leadership. Demonstrated ability to bring a metrics driven culture enabling accountability and decision making with a sense of urgency 
Strong analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making skills 
Ability to collaborate well with peers and internal/external stakeholders 
Experience working with large global organizations 
A track record of building high-performing, self-sufficient teams and delivering results in a fast-paced, quick-changing environment. 
Develop and operationalize strategies that create a best-in-class customer experience 
Advocate for the customer, working across product engineering, marketing, and operations to create a more aligned and cohesive customer experience 
